<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Conversion of an Existing Depository Institution to a Savings Bank</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.    Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Conversion of an Existing Depository Institution to a Savings Bank
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Office of the Commissioner of Savings & Residential Finance<BR>
Thrift Corporate Affairs Division<BR>
205 West Randolph, Suite 1900<BR>
Chicago, Illinois 60606-1811<BR>
(312) 793-1450<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
205 Illinois Compiled Statutes 205/8012 (Savings Bank Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
38 Illinois Administrative Code 1075
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Any depository institution (a commercial or savings bank, a savings / loan association, trust company, homestead, building and loan association, cooperative bank, industrial bank or a credit union) may convert into an Illinois Savings Bank. Conversion to a Savings Bank must be complete within 6 months of the date of board resolutions. This time may be extended for good cause. Charters are perpetually valid.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must complete and submit an "Application for Conversion of an Existing Depository Institution into an Illinois Savings Bank" to the Commissioner of Savings and Residential Finance (the Commissioner) and record with the County Clerk a savings bank charter in the county of the company's headquarters. Written notice must be given to the original chartering authority of the intention to convert the institution to a savings bank. Upon approval by the Commissioner, applicants must give written notification to the chartering authority. Applications may be denied if the applicant does not comply with the statute or regulations. Denied applications may be corrected and resubmitted to the Commissioner. Applications are usually processed within 4-6 weeks.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites, Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Pre-Requisite:</EM> Applicants must obtain insurance of their accounts from a deposit insurance corporation and pay any outstanding bills and assessments associated with the original charter.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
