<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License to Broker, Fund, Originate, Service or Purchase Residential Mortgage Loans</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License to Broker, Fund, Originate, Service or Purchase Residential Mortgage Loans
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Office of the Commissioner of Savings & Residential Finance<BR>
Mortgage Banking Division<BR>
205 West Randolph, Suite 1900<BR>
Chicago, Illinois 60606-1811<BR>
(312) 793-1450<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
205 Illinois Compiled Statutes 635/1-1 et seq. <BR>
(Residential Mortgage License Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
38 Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter 8, Part 1050
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The purpose of this Act is to protect consumers seeking residential mortgage loans and to ensure that the residential mortgage lending industry is operating fairly, honestly, efficiently, and is free from deceptive and anti-competitive practices. Any person, partnership, association, corporation or other entity brokering, funding, originating, servicing, or purchasing a residential mortgage loan must be licensed by the Commissioner of Savings & Residential Finance (the Commissioner). Each location of the business entity must be registered with the Commissioner. Licensees violating this Act  are subject to an injunction, business offense and a fine of up to $5,000. Unlicensed persons violating this Act may be subject to enforcement action and a fine of up to $5,000. Licenses are valid for 1 year. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must submit to the Commissioner, an "Application to Operate as a Residential Licensee, a list of any judgments entered against the applicant and bankruptcy petitions for the preceding 10 years, affirmation of age and financial solvency, and information on character, fitness, financial and business responsibility, background, experience and criminal record of the applicant. Investigations are performed to assure financial responsibility, experience, character and general fitness of the business entity. Application packages usually take 30 days to process.  Applications may be denied for failure to demonstrate net worth, financial responsibility, experience, or general fitness of the applicant. Decisions may be appealed through the Commission. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites, Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Pre-Requisite:</EM> All mortgage bankers must have a net worth of $100,000, and a surety and fidelity bond. Brokers must have a net worth of $35,000 and a surety bond. Post-Requisite: Licensees must submit an annual certified audit and an annual report of brokerage, mortgage and/or servicing report. The affairs of licensees are examined as the Commissioner deems necessary, but at least every 3 years. If the residential mortgage is being transferred for service to another mortgagor, information on that transfer business must be submitted to the borrower by both the transferor and the transferee of the mortgage.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License fee $1,800 ($1,000 at time of application and $800 upon approval)<BR>
Examination fee $400 per day, per examiner<BR>
Change of ownership fee $500<BR>
Change of name, address or officer fee $50<BR>
Late audit fee $50 per day<BR>
Full service office fee $250<BR>
Hearing fees $500<BR>
Investigation fee $1,000<P> 

The license fee for not-for-profits may be waived by submitting an application.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
