<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Real Estate License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Real Estate License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Office of the Commissioner of Savings & Residential Finance (CSRF)<P>
<PRE>
		Real Estate Division			Real Estate Division
		205 West Randolph, Suite 400 		500 East Monroe, Suite 200
		Chicago, Illinois 60606-1811		Springfield, Illinois 62701
		(312) 793-8704			        (217) 782-2991
</PRE>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 455  (The Real Estate License Act of 1983)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 1450, Illinois Administrative Code  60(7)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A License is required to conduct business as a real estate broker or salesperson. Licenses are valid for two years and allow the holder to conduct the business of selling, buying, exchanging, renting or leasing real estate. Conducting business without a license is subject to civil penalties up to $10,000.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must submit to CSRF an application provided by the Real Estate Division or designated vendor. The appropriate forms for a licensure must be filed within one year after receiving a passing score on the qualifying examination or credit for the examination terminates. The CSRF may refuse to issue or renew a license, may place on probation, suspend or revoke any license or may reprimand or impose a civil penalty for cause including fraud, misrepresentation, or criminal conviction.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Pre-Requisites:</EM> Real Estate Salesperson License:  must be 21 years old, of good moral character and have a high school diploma or GED, have successfully completed 30 classroom hours at a real estate school approved by the Illinois Real Estate Division and pass a written examination. Applicants between 18-21 years of age, may qualify if they have successfully completed at least 2 years of college as a full-time student, including the 30 classroom hours of study at a school approved by the Real Estate Division. Real Estate Broker License: must be at least 21 years old, have been actively practicing as a licensed salesperson for 1 of the last 3 years and have a bachelor's degree with a minor in real estate, or have successfully completed 90 classroom hours at a real estate school approved by the Illinois Real Estate Division.  Experience must be completed before taking the broker examination. To receive credit toward this experience requirement, an applicant must have held an active salesperson license and must submit verification as required by this office. This information will be verified by the Real Estate Division prior to the issuance of a license.<P>

Applicants may qualify for either license, if they are at least 21 years old, and have been admitted to practice law by the Illinois Supreme Court and possess a current Illinois attorney registration pocket card certificate. <P>

All coursework (with the exception of the bachelor's degree qualification) must have been completed at a real estate school approved by the Illinois Real Estate Division and  must be verified by submitting an original Uniform Real Estate Transcript bearing an embossed seal. This Transcript is valid for 5 years after the completion of the course. <P>

<EM>Corporations:</EM> Every officer actively participating in the real estate activities of the corporation must hold a license as a real estate broker, and every employee who acts as a salesperson for the corporation must hold a license as a real estate broker or salesperson. <P>

<EM>Partnerships: </EM>Every general partner must hold a license as a real estate broker, and every employee who acts as a salesperson for the partnership must hold a license as a real estate broker or salesperson. <P>

<EM>Limited Liability Companies:</EM> Every managing broker in a limited liability company must hold a license as a real estate broker or salesperson.<P>

Applications for an initial license must be accompanied by appropriate documentation and sponsor card issued by a licensed broker.<P>

No corporation / partnership / limited liability company will be licensed to conduct a brokerage business where an individual salesperson or group of salespersons owns or directly or indirectly controls more than 49% of the shares of stock or other ownership in the corporation/partnership/limited liability company. <P>

<EM>Co-Requisites:</EM> Licensees are required to carry a "pocket card" as proof licensure. Brokers must maintain an office or definite place of business within Illinois and must conspicuously display an identification sign of adequate size and visibility on the outside of the office and must display the certificate at that location. Certificates of all brokers and salespersons associated with or employed by the place of business must also be displayed. Licensees who have had a license for less than 15 years as of January 1, 1992, (except those licensees who fall within Article 3, Section 37.1 of the Act) are required to have 12 hours of continuing education as a condition for renewal of a license. <P>
</DD></DL>
<HR>

<H3>VII.	Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Salesperson 	Initial License	$100<P>
<DL><DD>
			Renewal			$25 per year<BR>
			Expired License	$50 plus all lapsed renewal fees<P>
</DD></DL>
Broker		Initial License	$100<P>
<DL><DD>
			Renewal			$50 per year<BR>
			Expired License	$50 plus all lapsed renewal fees<P>
</DD></DL>
Partnerships/Limited Liability Companies/Corporations<P>
<DL><DD>
			Initial License	$100<BR>
			Renewal 			$50 per year<BR>
			Expired License	$50 plus all lapsed renewal fees<P>
</DD></DL>
Branch Office	Initial License	$100<P>
<DL><DD>
			Renewal 			$50 per year<BR>
			Expired License	$50 plus all lapsed renewal fees<BR>
			Duplicate/Replacement License		$25<P>
</DD></DL>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
