<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for New and Used Vehicle Dealers</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.    Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for New and Used Vehicle Dealers
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.   Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Office of the Secretary of State of Illinois<BR>
Vehicle Services Department<BR>
Dealer/Remitter Licensing Section<BR>
Howlett Building, Room 069<BR>
Springfield, IL  62756<BR>
(217) 782-7817<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
625 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/5-100  (Illinois Vehicle Code), 92 Illinois Administrative Code Ch II, Section 1020.10,  .450 &  .470.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A license is required to sell or deal in new and used vehicles of any make, on consignment or otherwise, or act as an intermediary or agent or broker for a licensed dealer or vehicle purchaser other than as a salesperson conducting business without a License is a civil offense subject to a fine of $300 per day.<P>

Annual licenses are valid up to one year and expire on the last day of December each year.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for a new or used vehicle Dealers License must file: <P>
<DL><DD>
1. A completed, signed and notarized Form # VSD-324.3<P>

2. A $20,000 bond or certificate of deposit for each location at which applicant intends to do business. (Form # RT DS-47.1) <P>

3. A certificate of insurance with liability coverage for each business location in the amounts of $100,00 for bodily injury, $300,000 for each accident, and $50,000 property damage or $350,000 combined single limits. The expiration date of the certificate of insurance must be December 31 of the license year or indicate that coverage is continuous until canceled (a certificate is not required for trailer/mobile home dealers)<P>

4. Proof that applicant has a tax number from the Illinois Department of Revenue<P>

5. A letter from the manufacturer showing authorization to sell their make of (new) vehicles<P>

6. A check or money order for appropriate fees.  Upon receipt of the above, the Secretary of State Department of Police will  conduct a background investigation of the applicant.<P>
</DD></DL>
The average processing time for this License application is 2 to 4 weeks.<P>

Applications may be denied if the applicant does not meet the Dealers' Established Place of Business requirements (the principle place where office, lot and business records are located). A hearing may be requested by the applicant to contest the denial.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.   Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Licensed dealers must  keep records for 3 years regarding the acquisition and disposition of every vehicle and essential vehicle parts in the dealer's possession or sold or transferred by them.<P>

Applicants must comply with the requirements of the Dealers' Established Place of Business, as described in Vehicle Dealers brochure Form RT DS-21.11.<P>

Licensees must secure a Certificate of Authority, declaring that they are licensed vehicle dealers, for each business location. <P>

Master plates and identification cards are available at a fee to licensees after securing a license.	<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
	Annual Certificate of Authority 	 		$50<BR>
		After June 15 but before December 31	$25<P>

	Annual Supplemental Certificate of Authority	$25<BR>
		June 15 but before December 31		$12.50<P>

	Annual fee for Master Plates				$36<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
