<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Vehicle Auctioneer License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.     Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Vehicle Auctioneer License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.   Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Office of the Secretary of State of Illinois<BR>
Vehicle Services Department<BR>
Dealer/Remitter Licensing Section<BR>
Howlett Building, Room 069<BR>
Springfield, IL  62756<BR>
(217) 782-7817<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute :</H3>
<DL><DD>
625 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/5-700
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV:  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A License is required for a person to engage in the business of auctioning vehicles for more than one owner.  (Exceptions to this requirement are municipalities and licensed vehicle dealers.)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.   Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must complete and file a signed and notarized application with the Secretary of 	State.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applications for a vehicle auctioneer license must be accompanied by:<P>
<DL><DD>
	$50 fee for the applicant's principle place of business and
	$25 fee for each additional place of business.
</DD></DL>
</DD></DL>

