<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Registration and Protection of Trademarks Servicemarks and Tradenames</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration and Protection of Trademarks Servicemarks and Tradenames
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Secretary of State<BR>
Department of Business Services / Trademark Division<BR>
Room 328 Howlett Office Building<BR>
Springfield, IL 62756<BR>
(217) 524-0400<BR>
TDD: (800) 252-2904 or (217) 524-1137 (hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
765 Illinois Compiled Statutes 1035
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Any person may register a mark which distinguishes their goods or services from those of others. This requirement is not compulsory. Registration of a trademark is effective for 10 years.  <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A "Trademark or Servicemark Registration Application" provided by the Secretary of State must be completed and filed with the Secretary's Office.  If the application meets all statutory requirements, a Certificate of Registration is issued along with a Letter of Acceptance. Applications are usually processed within 1 week of receipt. If the application does not meet the requirements, it is returned to the applicant with an explanation of its denial. Denied applications may be corrected and resubmitted.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Pre-Requisite:</EM> The mark must be in-use in the State of Illinois before it may be registered. Examples of how the mark is currently being used must be submitted with the application.<P>

<EM>Co-Requisite:</EM> Applicants must notify the Secretary of State of any change in address. A name change by the applicant or a change of ownership must be filed on an Assignment application furnished by the Secretary.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
New Registration:							$10<BR>
Renewal Registration:						$ 5<BR>
Assignment of a Mark (Includes name changes):	$ 2<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

