<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Formation of a Registered Limited Liability Partnership (RLLP)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement  Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Formation of a Registered Limited Liability Partnership (RLLP)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Secretary of State<BR>
Department of Business Services / (RLLP) Division<BR>
Room 359 Howlett Office Building<BR>
Springfield, IL 62756<BR>
(217) 524-8008<BR>
TDD:  (800) 252-2904 or (217) 524-1137 (hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
805 Illinois Compiled Statutes 205 (Uniform Partnership Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
14 Illinois Administrative Code, Subtitle A, Chapter I / 165
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The partners, when organized under this Act are not liable for the debts, obligations, and liabilities of, or chargeable to the partnership. The true name of the (RLLP) must include the words "Registered Limited Liability Partnership" or the abbreviation "L.L.P." or the designation "LLP" as the last words or letters of its name. LLPs are effective for 1 year at which time the application must be renewed to remain in effect.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Limited Liability Partnerships (LLP) are created by filing an "Application for Registration of a Registered Limited Liability Partnership" with the Secretary of State. The LLP is not effective until the filing date or by a delayed date specified within the application. The initial / renewal application need only be signed by 1 authorized partner. Applications may be denied for non-compliance with the Act. Denied applications may be corrected and resubmitted.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Pre-Requisite:</EM> Applicants must provide a Federal Employee Identification Number (FEIN) to the Secretary of State, appoint and maintain a registered agent and a registered office in the State of Illinois, and state the address of its principal office, the number of partners, and the business mission statement along with their four-digit business code number.<P>

<EM>Co-Requisite:</EM> Renewal applications must be filed during the 60 day period preceding the anniversary of the original registration file date and must be submitted on the form prescribed by the Secretary of State.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Application for Registration	$100 per partner<BR>
Withdrawal				$100<BR>
File copies & Certificates	$25<BR>
Renewal Application			$100 per partner<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
