<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Shippers or Carriers of Hazardous Materials on Illinois roads must to comply with Federal and Illinois Hazardous Materials Regulations.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>


<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Shippers or Carriers of Hazardous Materials on Illinois roads must to comply with Federal and Illinois Hazardous Materials Regulations.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<PRE>
IL Dept of Transportation			Illinois State Police
Commercial Vehicle Safety Section		Commercial Vehicle Enforcement
3215 Executive Park Drive			500 Iles Park Place
Springfield, IL 62703				Springfield, IL 62718
(217) 785-1181					(217) 782-8097
</PRE>
</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>	
<DL><DD>
430 Illinois Compiled Statutes 30 / Sections 1-16.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 92, Illinois Administrative Code, Parts 102, 107-108, 171-173, 177-180.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Vehicles transporting hazardous materials over Illinois highways must conform to federal and state regulations governing the transportation of hazardous materials.<P>

The purpose of the federal and state Hazardous Materials Regulations are to ensure the safe handling, loading and transportation of hazardous materials on the nation's highways.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Commercial vehicles transporting hazardous materials on the state highways are subject to roadside inspection by the Illinois State Police.  All violations of the Hazardous Materials Regulations are then adjudicated by the Illinois Department of Transportation.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Operators of vehicles transporting hazardous materials must have a Commercial Drivers License with the appropriate endorsements and must register with the federal government as a Hazardous Materials Hauler.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

