<hr>
<h4>
<p>Business development centers counsel, conduct research, and train business people in a wide variety of business topics. They provide comprehensive information services and access to experts in many fields. Centers develop and maintain partnerships among community organizations and local, state and federal agencies, providing a focal point for broad networks of public and private resources at the community level. These partnership programs and activities serve small business and contribute significantly to the economic growth in Illinois.

<p>The Illinois Small Business Development Center Network of the Department of Commerce & Community Affairs (DCCA) offers Illinois' companies an invaluable business asset -- resources. The Illinois Small Business Development Center Network provides prospective and existing business owners with a variety of business resource programs.
</h4>


