<HEAD><TITLE>DCCA: News Release -- November 13, 1996</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000080" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#8080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/logosm.jpg" alt="DCCA Logo" width=165 height=82 align=left>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<h3>
Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p>
</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<font size=+3>1996 News Releases</font>
<br clear=right>
<hr>
<h3 align=center>
November 13, 1996<p>
Illinois Plastics Summit to be Held this Month
</h3>

<strong>CHICAGO, ILL.</strong> --  Illinois First and The Society of the Plastics Industry, Inc. will co-sponsor the Illinois Plastics Summit, to be held November 19, 1996 in Oak Brook, Illinois.  The event will focus on the identification of key issues facing the plastics industry, and offer recommendations to address industry concerns.<p>

"Businesses with a stake in the plastics industry are urged to attend this summit," said Illinois Department of Commerce and Community Affairs (DCCA) director Dennis Whetstone.  "Participants will be asked to identify what barriers impede their progress in Illinois, and we will create an action plan aimed at potentially resolving those issues."<p>

DCCA is a partner in Illinois First, a public/private resource team dedicated to assisting manufacturers interested in expanding, modernizing, relocating, training retraining or developing new technologies.<p>

Since its inception earlier this year, Illinois First has contacted 320 manufacturers.  The response has been gratifying with 70 businesses receiving information or technical assistance with concerns ranging from environmental issues to site selection.<p>

The Society of the Plastics Industry, Inc. is a trade association of nearly 2,000 members representing all segments of the plastics industry in the United States.<p>

For more information and registration, contact SPI's Midwest Regional Office, (773) 380-0808.<p>

<center><strong>###</strong></center>
	 
