<hr>
<h3 align=center>
August 9, 1996<p>
DCCA Welcomes State Fair Visitors to the Ethanol Exposition
</h3>

<strong>SPRINGFIELD, IL</strong> -- The Illinois Department of Commerce and Community Affairs (DCCA) invites fairgoers to visit the Fifth Annual Ethanol Expo and register for a chance to win a John Deere Gator all-terrain vehicle provided by the Illinois Corn Growers' Association, CIBA and Brownfield Network.<p>

The Ethanol Expo will provide fairgoers with free popcorn and ice water, courtesy of Archer Daniels Midland Corporation; Growmark, Inc.; the Illinois Corn Growers' Association; DCCA; the Illinois Department of Agriculture; Midwest Grain Products, Inc.; and Pekin Energy Company.<p>

"Illinois is the leading producer of ethanol fuel in the country," said Lt. Gov. Bob Kustra, the Governor's senior advisor for economic development.  "This exhibit gives visitors a chance to learn more about this clean alternative fuel, and our aggressive promotion and demonstration programs."<p>

Fairgoers can take a break from the heat by sitting in the comfort of the air-conditioned "Corn Bus," one of the 14 ethanol-powered buses currently operating in Peoria.  The Greater Peoria Mass Transit Authority is the first in the nation to use ethanol-fueled buses for transportation.  The Corn Bus operates on 93 percent ethanol and is painted to resemble an ear of corn, serving as a moving reminder of the benefits of ethanol fuel.<p>

Friday August 16, the Expo will feature Ford Motor Company.  On display will be the 1996 flexible-fueled ethanol-powered Ford Taurus.  In addition to the Taurus, the Expo will also feature Ford's recycling display and one of its flexible-fuel vehicle engines.  Ford Motor Company is one of the leading manufacturers using recycled materials in the production of its vehicles.  The Expo also will feature the pre-production E-85 Chevrolet S-10 pickup truck and several E-85 Chevrolet Lumina autos.<p>

The Ethanol Exposition is open from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. daily throughout the 1996 Illinois State Fair, August 9-18.<p>
###


