<h3>
Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p>
</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<font size=+3>1996 News Releases</font>
<br clear=right>
<hr>
<h3 align=center>
July 10, 1996<p>
</h3>

<H3 align=center>OUTDOOR RECREATION SUPER STORE EXPECTED TO BOOST ILLINOIS TOURISM</H3>

<STRONG>GURNEE, ILL.</STRONG> --  Gov. Jim Edgar today congratulated Bass Pro Shops Outdoor World on the company's decision to build a 125,000 square foot super store featuring shopping and entertainment facilities at Gurnee Mills Mall.<P>

"Tourism is an important industry in this state and contributes nearly $16 billion to the Illinois economy every year," the Governor said.  "Gurnee Mills Mall has quickly become a leading travel destination, and Bass Pro Shops Outdoor World will lend new appeal for those who enjoy the abundant natural resources of Illinois and the entire Upper Midwest.<P>

"My administration and Bass Pro Shops also share a commitment to conservation programs and encouraging outdoor recreation.  Since 1991, we have significantly expanded opportunities for recreational activities such as fishing and bicycling, and acquired and begun the development of site M in central Illinois, at more than 15,000 acres the largest property for outdoor recreation owned by the state.  Illinois and Bass Pro Shops Outdoor World are a perfect match."<P>

In addition to separate departments for activities such as fishing, hunting and camping, the store will feature such attractions as a four-story natural stone waterfall and a rough-hewn log cabin with a turning waterwheel and stocked trout pond.<P>

The store will be the company's third in the nation and first in the Upper Midwest.  It is expected to open next spring and will employ about 300 workers.<P>

My administration and Bass Pro Shops share a commitment to conservation programs and encouraging outdoor recreation," Edgar said.  "Since 1991, the state has significantly expanded opportunities for recreational activities such as fishing and bicycling.  In addition, we have acquired and begun the development of more than 15,000 acres of site M in central Illinois, the largest property for outdoor recreation and nature presenvation owned by the state.<P>

"Illinois and Bass Pro Shops Outdoor World are a good match because we understand the importance of preserving open space and recreation opportunities for future generations," the Governor said.<P>

The Gurnee Mills Bass Pro Shops Outdoor World will be modeled after the company's flagship store in Springfield, MO, ranked as Missouri's number one tourist attraction with more than four million visitors annually.  Bass Pro also supports numerous conservation efforts at the state and national levels. 	<P>

John L. "Johnny" Morris, President of Bass Pro Shops, said the company conducted an  extensive search of the Chicago and Milwaukee markets and chose Gurnee Mills as the best possible location for the new store.<P>

"There are significant numbers of fishing, hunting and outdoor enthusiasts in these markets, and we look forward to providing them with a great retail experience," Morris said.<P>

Laurence C. Siegel, Chairman and CEO of the Mills Corporation, said, "Bass Pro Shops Outdoor World will be a great addition to Gurnee Mills.  It's a terrific blend of entertainment and shopping, with a great commitment to customer service."<P>
  
Developed in 1991 by the Mills Corporation of Washington, D.C., Gurnee Mills Mall is the Midwest's largest enclosed discount/outlet center, combining manufacturer's outlets, department store outlets, specialty store outlets and value discount retailers.<P>


