<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>DCCA: 1995 Annual Report -- Director's Message</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000080" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/logosm.jpg" alt="DCCA Logo" width=165 height=82 align=left>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<h3>
Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p>
</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>

<FONT SIZE=+3>1995 Annual Report: Director's Message</FONT>
<BR CLEAR=RIGHT>
<hr>
<p>
When I returned to DCCA in Fiscal 1995, I returned with a clear agenda.  One of my first goals was to do everything I could to again enhance the visibility and credibility of the agency, both within state government and in the eyes of our constituents and customers.<p>  

DCCA was created in 1979 to coordinate and run services and programs in an integrated way so as to best serve the needs of businesses, local governments and the recipients of human services programs.  In recent years, the agency lost some of that focus by trying to do too many things without a sufficient resource base.<p>  

It's time to get back to the basics.<p>  

Illinois and DCCA have many opportunities.  But, in the past, many of those opportunities have been overshadowed by unnecessary bureaucracy, unneeded paperwork, cumbersome procedures and processes, and onerous rules and regulations.  Although some of this is necessary to ensure the public's trust and our accountability, I challenged the DCCA staff to start thinking of ways to streamline and improve processes and procedures to achieve efficiencies, both internally and externally.<p>

DCCA today has begun the process of "market-testing" its programs to ensure that they are demand-driven and truly responsive to the needs of customers.  We are working closer than ever to forge new partnerships with major business and local government organizations and serve as an outspoken advocate for our mutual constituents.<p>  

We're working to build the foundations that can lead to prosperous industries, rising real incomes and more quality jobs for our workers.  That's economic development and that's what we do.<p>

On the cover of this Annual Report you will see DCCA's Mission Statement.  Although the language in this Mission Statement was finalized in Fiscal Year 1996, its seeds were planted in Fiscal Year 1995.<p>  

I pledge to you our continued dedication to this mission.<p>


<P>
<HR>
