SA-Seasonally Adjusted<br>
AR-Annual Rate<p>

<hr>
<h3>ILLINOISANS  INCREASE  PERSONAL INCOME IN 1995</h3>

Per capita personal income rose $1,156 last year reaching an average of $24,763 for each state resident in 1995.  The 4.9 percent increase moved the state to eighth place from ninth the previous year.  Illinois was the only state in the Midwest to appear in the top 10, with eastern states heading the listing.<p>  

Illinois also placed highly in total personal income with its $293 billion overall amount, ranking fifth among the states.  The 5.6 percent growth in 1995 was slightly below the 6 percent national increase, as farm income declined last year.<p>

<hr>
<h4>TOP  STATES  BY  PER  CAPITA  INCOME      </h4>
<pre>
<strong>RANK                    STATE                     DOLLARS</strong>
 1                      CONNECTICUT              $30,303
 2                      NEW JERSEY                28,858
