<head><TITLE>College of Life Sciences - Science in the Evening</TITLE>
</head>
<!--body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#2F4F2F" vlink="#D98719" alink="#FFFFFF"-->
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<img src="evening.gif" alt="Science in the Evening">
<p>
<hr>

<blockquote>
Since the fall semester of 1995, the College of Life Sciences has offered a 
number of existing <a href=shadygrove.html>graduate</a> and 
<a href="9701.html">undergraduate</a> courses through a new continuing 
education program.  Credits from these evening courses will be equivalent to those 
obtained through the usual daytime undergraduate courses.  An 
<a href="mcat.html">MCAT preparation course</a> will be offered during the 
<a href=mcat4.html>intercession</a> and also in the evenings during the 
<a href=mcat5.html>Spring semester</a>.  In addition, a 
<a href="http://www.inform.umd.edu:8080/EdRes/Colleges/LFSC/life_sciences/.plant_biology/.WWW/duke.html">mini-medical
botany course</a> will be offered during the winter intercession.
<p>

<address>For further information, or to register, contact:
Dr. Lucinda Jack, (301) 405-0316, <a href="mailto:evening@life.umd.edu"> 
EVENING@LIFE.UMD.EDU</a></address>
</blockquote>

