	The <b>final examination</b> (250 points) has been scheduled <u>by the
University</u> for:<p>
<p>
		Wednesday, 22 May, 8:00 AM in ZOP 1240<p>
<b><u><p>
Regrade Policy</u></b>:<p>
<p>
	An examination may be returned to my staff for regrading <u>only</u> if the
total points were incorrectly totaled or if your answer can be documented by
text materials.  We will not consider answers which were misinterpreted by the
grader due to sloppy handwriting, poor organization, or incorrect terminology.
Your answers must be clear and concise the first time. A general plea for help
or a nonspecific request will not be honored.<p>
<p>
	An examination must be resubmitted to my staff by placing it in the box in the
laboratory within one week (7 days) of its return to you.  It must be
accompanied by a <b><u>TYPED</u></b> concise, brief (maximum of one (1) page)
summary of rebuttal or explanation.  Examinations written in pencil, turned in
after one week, or handed to staff member will not be considered.  Some of the
graded examinations will be photocopied before their return to discourage
academic dishonesty.<p>
<b><u><p>
Make-Up Examinations</u></b>:<p>
<p>
	Please refer to the current edition of the UMCP Undergraduate Catalog for
policies and procedures.  These regulations (<b><u>including the requirement
for documentation</u></b>) will be strictly enforced.<p>
