<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>The Paynter Lab</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BACKGROUND="Images/back4.gif"> 
<!IMG  align=right WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=75 ALT="crab/oyster picture"
SRC="Images/craboystersLG.jpg">

<H1>The Paynter Lab</h1>
<h2>at the University of Maryland College Park<BR>
College of Life Sciences</H2><BR>
<IMG WIDTH=500 HEIGHT=7  SRC="Images/strip.gif">
<HR>
<IMG  align=right WIDTH=250 HEIGHT=175 ALT="oyster picture" SRC="Images/oys2small.jpg">
<H3>Here we examine the physiological and biochemical mechanisms of life in the
estuary.  The Eastern oyster, <I>Crassostrea virginica</I>, is the model animal
we employ most of the time but we also study the mummichog, <I>Fundulus
heteroclitus</I>, as well as other bivalves including <I>Mercenaria
mercenaria</I>, <I>Geukensia demissa</I>, <I>Mya arenaria</I>, and <I>Macoma
baltica</I>.<BR></H3>
<P>
<!IMG  WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100  SRC="Images/craboystersLG.jpg">
<!IMG  WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100  SRC="Images/fundulusLG.jpg">
<!IMG  WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100  SRC="Images/MarshLG.jpg">
<P>Click for full sized images
<P>
<a href="Images/craboystersLG.jpg"><IMG WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=75 ALIGN=abs SRC="Images/craboystersLG.jpg" ></a>
<a href="Images/fundulusLG.jpg"><IMG WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=75 ALIGN=abs SRC="Images/fundulusLG.jpg" ></a>
<a href="Images/MarshLG.jpg"><IMG WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=75 ALIGN=abs SRC="Images/MarshLG.jpg" ></a>

<P>
	
