</a>
<center>
<h3> University of Maryland<br>College of Life Sciences<br>Graduate Programs<br></h3>
<strong><font size=+3>Chemistry (CHEM) and Biochemistry (BCHM)</font></strong><br>
</center>
<p>
<hr size=8 width=60%>
<br clear=left><br>
<p>
<a href="http://www-chem.umd.edu">
<i>Click here or on the picture to go to Chemistry & Biochemistry home page</i></a>
<p>
The department is a national leader in the number of grants and contracts
awarded.  Modern instrumentation supports research efforts in all the major
areas of chemistry and biochemistry including state-of-the-art analytical
services and x-ray crystallographic/graphics facilities for student and 
faculty use.
<p>
<strong>Requirements for Admission:</strong><p>
<ul>
<li>A B.S. in chemistry or biochemistry
<li>An overall grade point average of 3.0 and a minimum of 3.0 in 
chemistry courses
<li>Submission of GRE Aptitude Test scores to the department (the Chemistry
or Biochemistry Advanced Test is desirable, but not required)
<li>Three letters of recommendation from professional or academic references
</ul>
<p>
