</a>
<center>
<h3> University of Maryland<br>College of Life Sciences<br>Graduate Programs<br></h3>
<strong><font size=+3>Plant Biology (PBIO)</font></strong><br>
</center>
<p>
<hr size=8 width=60%>
<br clear=left><br>
<p>
<a href="http://www.inform.umd.edu:8080/EdRes/Colleges/LFSC/life_sciences/.plant_biology/.WWW/firstpge.html">
<i>Click here or on the picture for the Plant Biology Home Page</i></a>
<p>
The department is internationally recognized for its outstanding
faculty, research programs, and graduate training.  Its state-of-the-art
research facilities include over 8,000 feet of greenhouse space,
growth chambers, incubators, coldrooms, and autoclaves.
<p>
<strong>Requirements for Admission:</strong><p>
<ul>
<li>A B.S. or advanced degree
<li>Demonstrated competence in general and organic chemistry,
calculus, physics, and the biological sciences.  Upper-level course work in
plant biology is desirable.
<li>An overall grade point average of 3.0
<li>Submission of GRE Aptitude Test scores to the department (the Biology
Advanced Test is desirable, but not required)
<li>Three letters of recommendation from professional or academic references
<li>A statement of purpose for pursuing the degree, including goals and objectives 
for future work in the field.
<li>Foreign students must meet the university standards of the International
Education Service, including submission of a recent TOEFL score.
</ul>
