<head><title>Graduate Lab courses at Shady Grove</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#fde1dd">
<center><br><h1><b>New for 1997!</h1>
<h1>Continuing Education in Molecular Biology and Genetics at the University of Maryland Shady Grove Campus</h1></b>
<HR><hr size=1>
</center>
<b>Hands-on  graduate level lab courses</b> conveniently timed over three weeks (six evenings (Tu, Th) and two weekends) given in the brand new teaching laboratories at the University of Maryland Shady Grove campus.<br>
<p>
<b> MOCB708A Basic Concepts in Microbial Genetics.</b>
 (2 credits) Instruction in bacterial growth, regulation, and gene transfer including transformation and transduction. (To be offered February 1997).
<br>
<p>
<b> MOCB708B Basic Concepts in Molecular Biology.</b> (2 credits) Instruction in site-specific mutagenesis, DNA cloning and sequencing, S1 nuclease protection, and PCR. (To be offered March 1997).
<p>
<b> MOCB708C Advanced Concepts in Molecular Biology</b> (2 credits) Instruction in site-specific mutagenesis, DNA cloning and sequencing, S1 nuclease protection, and PCR. (To be offered April 1997).


