<p>
<b>Registration	</b>A registration package, explaining the 
registration proceedure may be mailed to prospective students.  
The students should follow the instructions in the cover letter 
and mail it back to Dr. Jack. (or slide it under her door, 1122 
Symons Hall). Students who register up to the first day of class 
will receive a balance due with their registration card in the 
mail.  <b>Late registrants need to pay their bill upon registration. </b> 
<p>													
<b>Parking </b>All students should park in PG2 <b>above </b>the 
meters.  It is free after 4 pm.
Note, please read the signs, the meters are in effect until 10 
pm.  Any student coming onto campus between 7 am and 4 pm should 
park in PG2 at the meters and pay.
<p>
<b>Pre-health information </b>Students who are uncertain which 
classes to take as prerequisites for the health professions 
should call the Health Professions Advising Office at 301-405-2793.
<p>
<b>First Day of Class </b>The Fall Semester starts on January 30.  
The first class will be the first LECTURE date that falls on or 
after January 30.  For example Biol 105 will start on Tuesday 
February  4, but Biol 222 with start on Thursday January 30.
<p>
<b>Full-time students </b>Please note that students will be charged 
the regular part-time per credit hour fee for these courses even 
if they have full-time status.  (This means that it is more expensive 
for a full-time student to take an evening course than a daytime course).
<p>
<h2>Classes Start January 30, 1997</h2>

<p>

More classes may be added.  For more information on registration for these
evening courses, or to be added to the mailing list, please contact
Dr. Lucinda Jack, 1122 Symons Hall, (301) 405-0316.<br>
<a href=mailto:evening@life.umd.edu>EVENING@LIFE.UMD.EDU</a>

