<head>
<TITLE>David Kirby</TITLE>
</head>
<body background="back4.gif">
<img align=right vspace=3 hspace=3 src="kirby.gif" alt="[picture of David Kirby]">
<H1>David Kirby</H1>
<B>Department of Zoology</B>
<BR>
<B>University of Maryland<br>
College Park, Maryland  20742</B>
<BR>
<B>email: <a href="mailto:dkirby@hamlet.umd.edu">dkirby@hamlet.umd.edu</a></B>
<BR>
<B>phone: (301) 405-6912</B>
<BR>
<HR>
<BR>
<B>Education </B>
<BR>
Ph.D. Candidate (Molecular Population Genetics) University of Maryland, 
College Park, MD; 1990 - Present.
<p>
B.S.- Ecology, Ethology and Evolution (Behavioral and Evolutionary Ecology emphasis) University of Illinois, Champaign, IL; May 1990.
<BR>
<BR>
<B>Publications</B>
<BR>
<BR>
1) Stephan, W. and D. A. Kirby. 1993.  RNA folding in Drosophila shows a distance effect for compensatory fitness interactions. Genetics 135: 97-103. 

<BR>
<BR>
2) Kirby, D. A., S. V. Muse and W. Stephan. 1995.  Maintenance of pre-mRNA secondary structure by epistatic selection. Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci., USA, (in press).

<BR>
<BR>

3) Kirby, D. A. and W. Stephan. 1995.  Positive selection in the <I>white</I>  gene of <I>Drosophila melanogaster</I>. Genetics, submitted.

<BR>
<BR>
<A HREF="kirbyabstract.html">click here to read Abstracts</A>
<BR>
<BR>
<B>Presented Papers</B>

<BR>
<BR>
1) Kirby, D. A. and W. Stephan. 1991.  Importance of secondary structure in pre-mRNA for 	genetic variation. Washington Area Population and Ecological Genetics Society. Washington, DC.

<BR>
<BR>
2) Kirby, D. A. and W. Stephan. 1992.  Secondary structures of small introns in precursor mRNA of the<I> Adh</I> locus in Drosophila. 33rd Annual Drosophila Research Conference. Philadelphia, PA.

<BR>
<BR>
3) Kirby, D. A. and W. Stephan. 1992.  Secondary structures of small introns in precursor mRNA of the <I>Adh</I> locus in Drosophila. International Conference on Molecular Evolution. Pennsylvania State University; University Park, PA.

<BR>
<BR>
