<head>
<title>University of Maryland
Molecular & Cell Biology Program</title> </head>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<h2>University of Maryland<br>
Molecular & Cell Biology Program </h2><a name ="list">

<h3>Research Facilities</h3>
State of the art facilities are available to students to conduct research in all aspects of cell and
molecular biology, including the preparation of cell cultures, monoclonal antibody production,
protein and nucleic acid analyses, peptide sequencing, oligonucleotide synthesis and sequencing,
fluorescence, scanning and transmission electron microscopy, computer graphics for molecular
modeling, NMR, and X-ray diffraction..<p>
<h3>Research Areas of MOCB Faculty</h3>
<h4><center>
<a href="biochem.html"><img src="red2.gif"> Biochemistry </a>
<a href="biophys.html"><img src="red2.gif">  Biophysics </a>
<a href="cell-bio.html"><img src="red2.gif"> Cell Biology  </a>
<a href="dev-bio.html"><img src="red2.gif"> Developmental Biology </a>
<a href="genetics.html"><img src="red2.gif"> Genetics </a><br>
<a href ="immunol.html"><img src="red2.gif"> Immunology </a>
<a href="neurobio.html"><img src="red2.gif"> Neurobiology </a>
<a href="oncology.html"><img src="red2.gif"> Oncology </a>
<a href="plantsci.html"><img src="red2.gif">  Plant Sciences </a>
<a href="prok-bio.html"><img src="red2.gif">  Prokaryotic Biology </a>
<a href ="virology.html"><img src="red2.gif">  Virology  </a>
</center></h4>

