<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>Oyster Stock Comparisons</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BACKGROUND="Images/back4.gif">
<h3>Current Projects in the Paynter Lab</h3>
							
<P>
<P>
<H4>Evaluation of American Oyster Stocks for Resource Rehabilitation:  Disease Resistance and Genetics.<P>
</H4>
<P><IMG ALIGN=Right SRC="Images/dbltrayLG.jpg" WIDTH=288 HEIGHT=216>

This project seeks to identify potentially useful differences in disease
tolerance among various populations of the eastern oyster, Crassostrea virginica,
found along the Atlantic and Gulf coast of North America.  It is being conducted
in collaboration with <A HREF="http://www.udel.edu/connie/gaffney"> Pat Gaffney</A> at the <A HREF="www.udel.edu/cms">University of Delaware</A> and  <A HREF="mailto:meritt@hpel.umd.edu">Don Meritt</A> at
the  <A HREF="http://www.cees.edu/hpel">University of Maryland Horn Point Laboratory</A>.   In 1995 we collected
broodstocks from various regions along the Atlantic and Gulf coast. In his
hatchery at Horn Point Don Meritt produced 9 populations of oysters representing
the various regions of broodstock origin including Texas and Louisiana
populations, North and South Carolina populations, Chesapeake Bay and Delaware
Bay populations.  Pat Gaffney will be performing genetic analyses on the groups
and we have deployed representative populations in low, moderate and high
salinity field sites in Chesapeake Bay.  It is our intention to determine whether
or not the oysters derived from more southern, disease-prone populations will
exhibit more tolerance to <I>Perkinsus marinus</I> infections compared to their
counterparts derived from more northern broodstocks.  Identifying differences
between groups may lead to productive breeding programs which will develop an
oyster more tolerant of <I>P. marinus</I> infection.

<P>Click for full sized images
<P>
<a href="Images/MjtrayLG.jpg"><IMG WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=75 ALIGN=abs SRC="Images/MjtrayLG.jpg" ></a>
<a href="Images/dbltrayLG.jpg"><IMG WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=75 ALIGN=abs SRC="Images/dbltrayLG.jpg" ></a>
<a href="Images/traycloseLG.jpg"><IMG WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=75 ALIGN=abs SRC="Images/traycloseLG.jpg" ></a>
<P>
<P>
<P>
  
