<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>CROSBreed</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BACKGROUND="Images/back4.gif"><H3>Current Projects in the Paynter Lab</H3><P>
 <H4>Cooperative Regional Oyster Selective Breeding (CROSBreed) Project.</H4><P>

<BR>


<IMG ALIGN=Right SRC="Images/oys2small.jpg" WIDTH=288 HEIGHT=216><P>As it's title
suggests, this project establishes a regional, cooperative selective oyster
breeding effort which hopes to produce oysters that are resistant or tolerant to
both <I>Haplosporidium nelsoni</I> (MSX) and <I>Perkinsus marinus</I> (Dermo).  Scientists from
New Jersey, Delaware, Maryland and Virginia are working together to expose large
groups of oysters to these disease in the field (Maryland and Virginia portions of Chesapeake Bay and Delaware Bay).  Survivors of the field
exposures will be sent back to the <A HREF="www.rutgers.edu">Rutgers</A> oyster hatchery to be used for the
production of additional, hopefully more tolerant lines. <P>


Funded by National
Oceanic and Atmospheric Association (NOAA) - National Marine Fisheries
Service/Sea Grant.</P><P>
<P>Click for full sized images
<P>
<a href="Images/MjtrayLG.jpg"><IMG WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=75 ALIGN=abs SRC="Images/MjtrayLG.jpg" ></a>
<a href="Images/dbltrayLG.jpg"><IMG WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=75 ALIGN=abs SRC="Images/dbltrayLG.jpg" ></a>

