<HTML> <HEAD><TITLE>Republication of The Oyster</TITLE></HEAD> <BODY
BACKGROUND="Images/back4.gif"><H3>Current Projects in the Paynter Lab</H3><P>

<H4>Republication of The Oyster by William Keith Brooks, Professor Emeritus,
Johns Hopkins University.</H4><P>

<BR>


First in 1891, and with a second edition in 1905, William Keith Brooks lamented
the decline of the oyster population in the Maryland portion of Chesapeake
Bay:<P>



<BLOCKQUOTE>	'We have wasted our inheritance by improvidence and mismanagement
and blind confidence; but even if our beds had held their own and were to-day as
valuable as they were fifty years ago, this would be no just ground for
satisfaction, in this age of progress, to a generation which has seen all our
other resources developed and improved.'<P> </BLOCKQUOTE>


<IMG ALIGN=Right SRC="Images/frontcover.jpg" WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=257>	<I>The
Oyster</I> is a popular  summary of a scientific study; a commentary on the
management of a valuable resource - the eastern oyster.  In 1882, Brooks was
appointed 'Oyster Commissioner' by the Governor of Maryland to 'examine the
oyster beds, and to advise as to their protection and improvement.'  Having
advised the Governor and the legislature that rampant overharvesting was
occurring and the immediate need for protective measures, he was disappointed to
see essentially nothing done to protect the oyster.  He wrote <I>The Oyster</I>
to better inform the layman about the animal itself and to press for better more
intelligent management of the resource.  Amazingly, many of his words and
recommendations are still relevant today.<P>



I have written an introduction to Brooks book which I hope will put his work into
the perspective of the present and allow the reader to understand just how
valuable his words were 100 years ago, and how valuable his advice remains
today.  The book is now available at most bookstores as part of the JHU Press Maryland Paperback Bookshelf.  Retail price:  $15.00.<P>
<P>
<P>
<P>Click for full sized images
<P>
<a href="Images/plate1.jpg"><IMG WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=75 ALIGN=abs SRC="Images/plate1.jpg" ></a>
<a href="Images/fpage.jpg"><IMG WIDTH=50 HEIGHT=75 ALIGN=abs SRC="Images/fpage.jpg" ></a>
<a href="Images/frontcover.jpg"><IMG WIDTH=50 HEIGHT=75 ALIGN=abs SRC="Images/frontcover.jpg" ></a>

<P>


<A HREF="http://www.jhu.edu:80/~jhupress"> <img WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=50
src="Images/JHUP3.gif"></A>

<P> <HR> <A HREF="PaynterLab.html">Return to Paynter Lab Homepage</A> </BODY>
