<html>
<title>CELLNET-ZOOLOGY 211 OnLine</title>

<body bgcolor=ffffff>
<Center>
<h2>CELLNET-ZOOLOGY 211 OnLine</h2>
</Center>

<blockquote>
Your Zoology 211 Course Staff, in the never ending quest for 
ways to enhance quality of life for Zoology 211 students, now 
presents CELLNET, a listserve designed to promote 
communication between students, staff and of course 
Drs. Know-It-All.  The time is NOW to subscribe to CELLNET 
(due to budget cuts, there will be no complimentary gifts for
subscribing).  CELLNET will be used to communicate 
information about the course to subscribers, and will 
provide a way for subscribers to pose questions about 
lectures to Drs. Know-it-All.  Responses to questions 
will be sent to CELLNET, such that all subscribers 
will see the question and receive the answer (who 
could ask for anything more!).  In addition, CELLNET 
will provide a convenient way to post lecture outlines and 
handouts, important information about lab, and other 
announcements of interest.<p>

<b>HOW CAN I BE PART OF THIS ZOOLOGY 211 
INFORMATION SUPERHIGHWAY?</b><p>

First, you must have a campus computer WAM account.  
If you do not already have a computer alias on campus, 
DO NOT PASS GO!  Students register electronically 
(see How to Register for a WAM Account in a WAM lab).  
Instead, proceed directly to the Computer Science Center, 
Room 3326.  Bring your student ID and current registration 
card with you. An account will be created for you by one 
of the counselors.<p>
If you do not already have a WAM account, there are plenty 
of other great things on the network (other than CELLNET) - 
for example, access to the ZOOL 211 World Wide Web home 
page, library card catalog, the daily news, lists of University 
events, and much more!<p>

<b>DO I HAVE TO HAVE MY OWN COMPUTER IN ORDER 
TO BE PART OF  CELLNET?</b><p>

No.  Any member of the UMD community can get a
campus computer account.  You can go to the computer 
science center WAM lab to log into your account, and 
retrieve your CELLNET messages<p>

<b>SUBSCRIBING TO CELLNET</b><p>
Next, you must SUBSCRIBE to CELLNET.  Subscription 
is done automatically by the listserv computer, and the process 
could not be simpler.<p>

<OL>
 <li>Enter you WAM account
 using you name and password (do not try to subscribe from an 
account other than your own, or all of your CELLNET mail 
will be directed to that account).
 <li>Once into your account, you must send a mail 
message to the University's listserv computer, asking
it to subscribe you to CELLNET.  Your message should be sent to:<p>

listserv@umdd.umd.edu<p>

         Your subscribe message is simply:<p>

<code>sub cellnet your name</code><p>

         Mail this message, and you will automatically be subscribed 
to CELLNET.  "sub" tells the listserv computer that you want to 
subscribe, "cellnet" is the name of the listserv your are subscribing 
to, and your name should follow.  That's it!<p>
</ul>
<b>GETTING OLD MESSAGES FROM CELLNET</b><p>

After subscribing to CELLNET, you will get a welcome message 
that includes some important instructions, e.g., how to retrieve 
previously sent or deleted messages.  DO NOT delete this 
original message!  To get a list of previously sent CELLNET 
messages, send an email to:  listserv@umdd.umd.edu .Do not put 
a subject heading on your memo and do not put any blank lines 
at the top of it.  Your message should read:<p>

<code>index cellnet</code><p> 

You will then receive a listing of these messages.  
Instructions for retrieving them from the list are contained in 
the original messages from listserve.

</body>
</html>
