<HR>

<A NAME=MembranePotentialAns>
<H3><P ALIGN=CENTER><B> Membrane Potentials Review:</B><BR>
<B><I> Answer Key</I></B></H3></P>

<P> #1. See your Textbook!!</P>

<BR>
<P> #2. The Nernst Equation is :</P>
&nbsp  V<sub>m</sub> = (RT/zF) ln [Ion]<sub>side1</sub>/[Ion]<sub>side2</sub> , where<BR> 
 &nbsp     R = gas constant (8.314 joules/deg mole)<BR>
 &nbsp     T = degrees Kelvin;<BR>
 &nbsp     z = valence or charge;<BR>
 &nbsp     F = Faraday's constant (96,500 coulombs/mole)</P>

<P> At a body temperature of 37o C, and plugging in the constants and converting to log 10, the equation becomes:</P>

<P>&nbsp    Vm (in mV) = (61.5/z) log 10 [Ion] 1/[Ion] 2</P>

<P> So  E Na+  = +61.5 mV ( inside of cell positive since Na+  moves in, down [DELTA]C) E K+  = -61.5 mV,<BR>
 E Ca++  = +123 mV (did you forget to divide by z which is 2 for calcium?), E Cl-  = - 61.5 mV</P>

<BR>
<P> #&nbsp3a. increase P of sodium or calcium or decrease P of potassium or chloride</P>

<OL TYPE=a START=2>
    <LI>  increase P of potassium or chloride (if V m did not = E Cl- ) or decrease P of sodium or calcium.
</OL>

<OL TYPE=a START=3>
    <LI>  increase potassium inside or decrease it outside decrease sodium outside or increase it inside increase calcium outside or decrease it inside
</OL>

<OL TYPE=a START=4>
    <LI>  reverse of &quot;c&quot; above
</OL>

<P> (Parts of question 3 assumes that each ion is somewhat permeable and that V m does NOT = the equilibrium potential for that ion.)</P>

<BR>
<P> #4a. At threshold (depolarization caused by stimulus or signal molecule), voltage-gated sodium channels open and membrane depolarizes, opening more channels. Sodium channels inactivate (close). This, combined with the opening of voltage-gated potassium channels (caused by depolarization due to entry into cell of sodium), causes repolarization. Cell may briefly hyperpolarize due to Vm going to equilibrium potential of potassium which is more negative that Vm. You should understand why this is so!</P>

<OL TYPE=a START=4>
    <LI>  See your text!!!
</OL>


</BODY>
