<HR></H2>

<OL TYPE=1 START=1>
 <LI><OL TYPE=a START=1>
 <LI>Top to bottom: 0 mV, + 123 mV, - 61.5 mV, and 220 mM</P>
 <LI>  - 61.5 mV (note: use most permeable ion in Nernst equation!)</P>
 <LI>  Not in this case since nothing else is very permeable! (tricky, I know)</P>
 <LI>  increase P of Lg-  and Nr+</P>
 <LI>  increase P of Px=  and Mz+  or decrease P of Lg-  and Nr+</P>
 <LI>  unmyelinated, adrenergic, excited by ACh on nicotinic receptor, arises from  paraverterbral ganglion, long fiber for diffuse innervation</P>
  <LI>  To plot this, begin at time 0 at the correct V m (-61.5 mV) go to equilibrium potential of Mz+  and after 1.5 msec go to equilibrium potential for Nr+  for 1.5 msec, and then go back to Vm</P>
 </OL>
   <LI><OL TYPE=a START=1>
