   <LI>1. Factor X is activated by Intrinsic and/or extrinsic pathways 2. Factor X converts Prothrombin to Thrombin 3. Thrombin converts fibrinogen to fibrin 4. Fibrin stabilizing factor covalently links loose fibrin threads into tight clot</P>
    <LI>  throbin is bound by fibrin threads and is destroyed by anti-thrombin
    <LI>  fibrinolysin
    <LI>  The erthyropoeitin feedback loop that begins with decreased delivery of oxygen to  the tissues, especially the kidneys, etc. Be sure to close the loop!
   </OL>

<P><LI>She cannot make anti Rh antibodies!</P>

<LI>How: Increased CO 2 leads to decreased plasma pH Why: to facilitate the unloading of more O 2 to the tissues in systemic capillaries P 50: it increases (as the affinity of Hb for O 2 decreases)</P>

