<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE> MAMPHYS directions</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<HR WIDTH="90%">
<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><B> MAMPHYS --- ZOOLOGY 422 / 423 OnLine</B></H1>
<HR WIDTH="90%">

<P><FONT SIZE="5"><B> Y</B></FONT>our Zoology 422/423 Course Staff, in the never ending quest for ways to enhance quality of  life  for Zoology  ZOOL  422/423  students,  now  presents<B> MAMPHYS</B> ,  a  listserv designed to promote communication among students, staff and of course Dr. Know-It-All. The time is NOW to subscribe to <B> MAMPHYS</B> (due to budget  cuts, there will be  no complimentary gifts  for  subscribing).<B> MAMPHYS</B> will  be  used  to  communicate information about the course to subscribers, and will provide a way for subscribers to pose questions about lectures to  Dr.  Know-it-All. Responses  to  questions  will  be  sent  to<B> MAMPHYS</B> , such that all subscribers will see the question and receive the answer (who could ask for anything more!). In addition, <B> MAMPHYS</B> will provide a convenient way to post  lecture  outlines  and  handouts, important information about  lab, and other announcements of interest.</P>

<BR><P> &#174;<B><I> HOW CAN I BE PART OF THIS ZOOLOGY 422/423 INFORMATION SUPERHIGHWAY?</I></B></P>

<P> First, you must have a campus computer WAM account.  If you do not already have a computer alias on campus, DO NOT PASS  GO! Students  can  register electronically (see How to Register for a WAM Account in a WAM lab).  Instead, proceed directly to the Computer Science Center, Room 3326.  Bring your student ID and current registration card with you.  An account will be created for you by one of the counselors.</P>

<P> Once you have a WAM account, notice the other great things on the network (other than <B> MAMPHYS</B> ) - for example, access  to  the  library card  catalog,  the  daily news, lists of University events, the ZOOL 422/423 WWW home page, and much more!</P>

<BR><P> &#174;<B><I> DO I HAVE TO HAVE MY OWN COMPUTER IN ORDER TO BE PART OF MAMPHYS?</I></B></P>

<P> No. Any member of the UMD community can get a campus computer account. You can go to the computer science center or WAM lab to log into your account, and retrieve your <B> MAMPHYS</B> mail.</P>

<BR><P> &#174;<B><I> SUBSCRIBING TO MAMPHYS</I></B></P>

<P> Next,  you  must<B> SUBSCRIBE</B> to <B> MAMPHYS</B> .  Subscription  is  done automatically by the listserv computer, and the process could not be simpler.</P>

<OL TYPE=1 START=1>
    <LI>  Enter your WAM account using your name and password (do not try to subscribe  from  an  account  other  than your own, or  all of your<B> MAMPHYS</B> mail will be directed to that account).
</OL>

<OL TYPE=1 START=2>
    <LI>  Once into your account, you must send a mail message to the University's listserv  computer,  asking  it  to  subscribe  you  to<B> MAMPHYS</B> .  Your message should be sent to:
</OL>

<BLOCKQUOTE>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsplistserv@umdd.umd.edu</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P> Your subscribe message is simply:</P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>&nbsp&nbsp&nbspsub MAMPHYS your name</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P> Mail this message, and  you  will  be  automatically  subscribed  to <B> MAMPHYS.</B> &quot;sub&quot; tells the listserv computer that you want to subscribe, &quot;MAMPHYS&quot; is the name of the listserv you are subscribing to, and <B> your name</B> should follow.  That's it!</P>

<BR><P> &#174;<B><I> GETTING OLD MESSAGES FROM MAMPHYS</I></B></P>

<P> After subscribing to <B> MAMPHYS</B> , you will get a welcome message that includes some important instructions, e.g., how to retrieve previously sent or deleted messages. DO NOT delete this original message! To get a list of previously sent<B> MAMPHYS</B> messages, send an email to: listserv@umdd.umd.edu Do ot put a subject heading on your memo and do not put any blank ilines at the top of it. Your message should read: index MAMPHYS You will then receive a listing of these messages and instructions for retrieving them.</P>


</BODY>
</HTML>
