<H2><A NAME="Heading1"> Answers for Exam 1, Spring, 1996 (page 96 in manual)</A></H2>

<HR>

<OL TYPE=1 START=1>
 <LI><OL TYPE=a START=1>
 <LI>Top to bottom: 0 mV, + 123 mV, - 61.5 mV, and 220 mM</P>
 <LI>  - 61.5 mV (note: use most permeable ion in Nernst equation!)</P>
 <LI>  Not in this case since nothing else is very permeable! (tricky, I know)</P>
 <LI>  increase P of Lg-  and Nr+</P>
 <LI>  increase P of Px=  and Mz+  or decrease P of Lg-  and Nr+</P>
 <LI>  unmyelinated, adrenergic, excited by ACh on nicotinic receptor, arises from  paraverterbral ganglion, long fiber for diffuse innervation</P>
  <LI>  To plot this, begin at time 0 at the correct V m (-61.5 mV) go to equilibrium potential of Mz+  and after 1.5 msec go to equilibrium potential for Nr+  for 1.5 msec, and then go back to Vm</P>
 </OL>
   <LI><OL TYPE=a START=1>
    <LI>  muscarinic and beta 2
    <LI>  alpha 1
    <LI>  muscarinic
    <LI>  muscarinic
    <LI>  beta 1
    <LI>  alpha 1
    <LI>  muscarinic
    <LI>  muscarinic
    <LI>  alpha 2 and beta 2
    <LI>  (I know, I put 2 j's) nicotinic
    <LI>  nicotinic
    <LI>  nicotinic
    <LI>  muscarinic
    <LI>  muscarinic
    <LI>  alpha 2
    </OL>

<P><LI>Type A &nbsp&nbsp A antigen and anti B<BR>
 &nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbspA and B antigens and neither anti A nor anti B</P>

<LI>See text figure for graph</P>
<LI><OL TYPE=a START=2>
    <LI>  plasma proteins that cannot cross capillary (impermeable solute)
    <LI>  See text figures
    <LI>  Edema
    <LI>  R - I or F - D F - I (initially to cause the edema) F - I R - I or F - D F - I or R - D
    </OL>

<LI><OL TYPE=a START=1>
   <LI>1. Factor X is activated by Intrinsic and/or extrinsic pathways 2. Factor X converts Prothrombin to Thrombin 3. Thrombin converts fibrinogen to fibrin 4. Fibrin stabilizing factor covalently links loose fibrin threads into tight clot</P>
    <LI>  throbin is bound by fibrin threads and is destroyed by anti-thrombin
    <LI>  fibrinolysin
    <LI>  The erthyropoeitin feedback loop that begins with decreased delivery of oxygen to  the tissues, especially the kidneys, etc. Be sure to close the loop!
   </OL>

<P><LI>She cannot make anti Rh antibodies!</P>

<LI>How: Increased CO 2 leads to decreased plasma pH Why: to facilitate the unloading of more O 2 to the tissues in systemic capillaries P 50: it increases (as the affinity of Hb for O 2 decreases)</P>

