<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE> 10 Hexamethonium Man</TITLE>
</HEAD>


<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<HR>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><B> The Hexamethonium Man</B></H2>

<HR>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><B> Starling's Law of the Heart</B></H2>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><B> and</B></H3>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><B> LSD and the Elephant</B></H2>

<HR>


<P> In 1954, W. D. M. Paton published an article in Pharmacological Reviews (volume 6, page 59) which describes the prolonged effects of the administration of hexamethonium, a potent antagonist of nicotinic receptors in the autonomic ganglia. This &quot;Hexamethonium Man&quot; article is a classic description of the consequences of losing the autonomic nervous system and should be read by every avid 422 fan.</P>

<P> You must also read a humorous description of Starling's Law of the Heart by A. C. Burton (1965). Burton's &quot;poetical summary&quot; is a classic piece of physiological wit. Please read it.</P>

<P> Finally, LSD: Its Effects on a Male Asiatic Elephant, an article (1962.<I> Science</I><B> 138</B> : 1100-1102) that describes science gone amok, is a real 'must read' piece of literature.</P>

<P> Copies of the first article is posted on the Web pages. Read it before the appropriate examination! The LSD article from <I> Science</I> and <I> Starling's Law</I>&nbsp may be obtained in your recitation session.</P>

<HR>

</BODY>
</HTML>
